  Source   Edit

This module implements callbacks for various stdlib and system functions. They are split up into multiple categories so that each can be separately registered via the registerOps procedures.

Imports

../ast/ast_types, ../ast/ast, ../ast/idents, ../ast/lineinfos, ../front/options, ../sem/sighashes, gorgeimpl, vmconv, vmdef, vmdeps, vmerrors, vmhooks, vmmemory, vmobjects, ../front/msgs, ../ast/reports_sem, ../ast/report_enums, ../modules/modulegraphs

    tags: [].}
Convenience proc used for setting up the callbacks relevant during compile-time execution. If disallowDangerous is set to 'true', all operations that are able to modify the host's environment are replaced with no-ops   Source   Edit
